The calling sequence is p -> s -> q -> r -> q.

Write the access links of the activation records to enable correct access to variables in the procedures from other procedures involved in the calling sequence.

Which of the following correctly describes the access link (static link) that each activation record must store to enable correct non-local variable access?
A. Each activation record stores a pointer to the activation record of the procedure that defined (statically enclosed) it.
B. Each activation record stores a pointer to the activation record of the procedure that called (dynamically invoked) it.
C. Access links are not required when all variables are global.
D. Access links point to the most recently created activation record on the stack.

Indicate the result of the following program if the language uses (i) static scope rules and (ii) dynamic scope rules.

var x, y: integer;
procedure A (var z: integer);
  var x: integer;
  begin
    x := 1;
    B;
    z := x
  end;
procedure B;
  begin
    x := x + 1
  end;
begin
  x := 5;
  A(y);
  write(y)
end.
